<P>&rx; <HI>Rad Aristoloch. rot.</HI> &ounce;<HI>j Herb. Ab&s;. vulg. Abrotan. faem. Tanacet Sabin. a Mj. Helleborast. M&s;s. Pulp. Colo|cynth. Aloes. a</HI> &dram;<HI>j f Dec. in aq</HI> lb<HI>iij ad</HI> lb<HI>ij col. pro fotu ope &s;tupharum Abdominis regioni calide u&s;urpan|do.</HI></P>
<P>After u&s;ing this <HI>Stupe</HI> or <HI>Fomentation,</HI> the following <HI>Pultice</HI> may be laid on the Navel.</P>
<P>&rx; <HI>Ther. Ven. Farin. Lupin. a</HI> &dram;<HI>iij &s;em Sancton</HI> &dram;<HI>i&s;s hier pier.</HI> &dram;<HI>&s;s Ol. Ab|&s;inth. Still. gt. xvj &s;ucc. Tanacet. a&s;. F. Catapla&s;ma</HI></P>
